news.title: Bengaluru citizens rue 'steepest-ever hike' in property tax
news.para: The hike, which the BDA quietly introduced in its property tax portal without prior notice, has triggered strong reactions as many property owners felt the BDA's conviction does not go beyond extracting taxes.

news.title: Lucknow development body to set up township along Agra expressway
news.para: The project spans across 12 villages in the Kakori region and will be developed in two phases—Phase I covering 1,893.93 acres and Phase II covering 3,716.14 acres.

news.title: Tamil Nadu to build one lakh houses under Rs 3,500 crore scheme for hut-dwellers
news.para: All houses on objectionable poramboke land, huts occupied by tenants, huts used for commercial purposes, huts with RCC, metal sheet roofs, and occupants who own a house elsewhere will not be eligible for the scheme.

news.title: No sale of terrace separately for commercial use: West Bengal government
news.para: ​The state urban development and municipal affairs department on Tuesday issued a 20-point guideline on specific precautionary measures for commercial use of buildings in all civic body jurisdiction areas across the state.

news.title: Eleannt Enterprises acquires plot in Delhi's Vasant Vihar for Rs 95 crore
news.para: The South Delhi-based real estate firm has paid Rs 6.65 crore as stamp duty and corporation tax, according to the copy of sale deed accessed by ET. Lokeshh Goyal, director of Eleannt Enterprises, declined to comment on the deal.

news.title: HDFC Capital Advisors settles AIF rule violation case with Sebi
news.para: ​HDFC Capital Advisors -- the investment manager of HDFC Capital Affordable Real Estate Fund-I (HCARE-1), an Alternative Investment Fund (AIF) -- had filed suo motu settlement applications under Sebi's settlement rules.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance's profit rises 21% to Rs 245 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income during the quarter under review rose to Rs 834 crore from Rs 692 crore in the year-ago period, Aadhar Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance reports consolidated profit at Rs 207.02 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: "In FY 2025, we disbursed Rs 3,604 crore, achieving a 15 per cent year-on-year growth. This reflects the strength of our operational execution and strategic focus, which also enabled us to grow our AUM by 25 per cent year-on-year," said MD of the company.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics exits from plywood business due to continued losses
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics, on Tuesday, declared its results for the March quarter, in which its consolidated profit declined 58.6 per cent to Rs 43.18 crore, due to settlement with JV partners and vendors of the plywood business.

news.title: Geberit posts 4.9% rise in sales to $1.07 billion in Q1 2025
news.para: "For 2025, we continue to expect stabilising market demand in Europe and a mixed environment overseas," Chief Executive Christian Buhl said on a conference call.

news.title: Over 2.7 lakh more houses to be built in Rajasthan under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: ​The CM stated that the newly sanctioned houses will benefit families identified in the 2018 Awas Plus survey, many of whom waited for permanent housing for over six years.

news.title: Form co-operative societies in Nashik to avail benefits: MHADA
news.para: MHADA authorities on Monday organised a Janata Durbar (people's court/assembly) on Monday, similar to Lok Shahi Din, during which residents approached the office for solutions to their grievances.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance plans to raise over Rs 6,000 crore in FY26
news.para: Sundaram Home Finance reported a 26 per cent rise in its net profit for the January-March 2025 quarter to Rs 71.57 crore from Rs 56.80 crore registered in the corresponding quarter of last financial year.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net operating income up 16% to Rs 488.5 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: The company announced the distribution of Rs 319.1 crore (Rs. 5.25 per unit) to its unitholders for the March quarter, 10.5 per cent higher than the fourth quarter of the 2023-24 fiscal, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Activists in Vasai Virar demand SIT probe into Illegal constructions
news.para: These unauthorised structures are putting excessive pressure on the city's infrastructure, affecting water, electricity, and transport services for legitimate tax-paying residents.

news.title: Haryana cabinet approves proposal to amend policy for fixation of land rates
news.para: The Haryana Government had formulated a policy for the fixation of land market rates across all departments, boards, corporations, panchayati raj institutions, and urban local bodies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh plans to build 60 lakh PMAY-Rural houses in FY26
news.para: The survey to assess the housing requirement started in Dec 2024 and ended in April 2025. During this period, the department received applications for over 54 lakh houses.

news.title: Housing board set to offer more than 150 plots in Siddharth Vihar, Ghaziabad
news.para: Spanning over 635 acres, the township along the Delhi-Meerut Expressway is barely a 30-minute drive from Noida City Centre and Connaught Place.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body plans crackdown on PGs lacking essential amenities
news.para: Over 1,800 PGs unauthorised, BBMP explores stricter policies to enforce civic rules, including legalising only those that meet hygiene and parking standards

news.title: Lucknow development body to begin registration of 2,502 flats in June
news.para: Under the new phase of Vishram Nagar, 1,832 EWS units (30–32 sqm), 214 LIG units (around 45 sqm), and 456 MMIG flats (approximately 55 sqm) are under construction.
